Input:

df1 = pd.DataFrame({
    'ID': [1, 2, 3],
    'Name': ['A', 'B', 'C']
})

df2 = pd.DataFrame({
    'ID': [1, 2, 4],
    'Marks': [90, 85, 70]
})


Output:

ID   Name   Marks
1    A        90
2    B        85
3    C       NaN


Solution:

merged = pd.merge(df1, df2, on='ID', how='left')
print(merged)
